    "summary": "I am a young scholar in the History and Philosophy of Economic Thought, who recently received his PhD at the University of Amsterdam on a history of Economic Planning in the Netherlands. Trained as a philosopher, I use the dictum that philosophy can be applied to all subjects as an excuse to engage in a wide variety of subject, from political theory, to intellectual history and political economy. My main research topic is the role economic experts play in modern governments. In particular, I am interested how modern economics shapes our conception of the future. This issue is intertwined with the philosophy of history; it asks the question how our conception of history is formed, by which experiences and by which scientific discourses; and how a shared time horizon is fundamental to our modern concept of politics.\n\nAreas of competente:\n- History of Economic Thought\n- Political Theory\n\nAreas of interest\n- Intellectual History/ History of Political Thought/ Conceptual history\n- History and Philosophy of Science\n- Science and Technology Studies\n- Political Economy\n\n- Topics I work on:\n- Future expectations in economic theory\n- The politics of Future-Making\n- Regimes of Historicity\n- Economic planning\n- Philosophy of History\n- Environmental economics",
